@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Bordo" where you want on
your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or Libraries are
needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench must have at least 8
colours.

                             How to play?

MAIN MENU

  When run, the game shows the main menu with the following buttons:

-About               -Displays the informations about 'Bordo'.

-Choose Your Colours -This button enters a menu where you can choose your
                      prefered tile colours and the game will use those
                      colours. The @{b}choosen@{ub} colours are 'pressed down'. To
                      select or unselect a colour, just click on it, this
                      will toggle it on or off. Note that you must choose
                      at least 4 different colours.

-Play!!              -To play the game.

GAMEPLAY

  To play, click on any tile located on the border of the game board, it can
be occupied by a triangular shaped icon or a coloured tile, all the tiles that
are located on the row or column corresponding to it will move by one position
toward the tile you clicked on. If you click on a corner tile, the tiles
located diagonally up to the opposing corner will move by one position toward
that tile. As the tiles are moved, if a coloured tile is located on the border
where you clicked on, it will go to the opposite side of the game board.

  By moving tiles around, when 3 tiles or more of the same colour are aligned
on the border, those will be removed and you will get points according to the
number of removed tiles, as shown in the following table:

   3 tiles:    1 point
   4 tiles:   10 points
   5 tiles:  100 points
   6 tiles:  360 points
   7 tiles:  490 points
   8 tiles:  640 points
   9 tiles:  810 points
  10 tiles: 1000 points

  As you can see the more tiles of the same colour you align, the more points
you make... especially if you make double alignments (one on each side of the
board).

  Continue the game until the board gets full, in which case the game ends.

  The game keeps the best score made since the game was run.

  You can abort a game at any time by clicking on the window's close button,
this will return to the main menu.

  Have fun!

@endnode

